FBIS3-8601 "dreeu049_c_94005" FBIS-EEU-94-049 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 CZECH REPUBLIC Denies Idea of Planned Attack on Slovakia LD1103220394 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 2000 GMT 11 Mar 94 LD1103220394 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network Language: Czech Article Type:BFN [Text] Czech Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus reacted to today's speech by [Slovak Prime Minister] Vladimir Meciar and observed that he was not present at his talks with Karel Pezl, [former] chief of the Czechoslovak Army General Staff, which reportedly took place during the meeting of the Council for State Defense on 28 September 1992. Klaus declined to comment on the absurd idea of a plan for a military attack against Slovakia and declared that he did not hold any talks with Meciar on this subject.
